That&amp;#039;s really all the info there is.  The installation files have not been altered in any way (other than being split onto 4-CDs).  You can install any one of the Window&amp;#039;s Vista versions (Home, Business, Ultimate, etc.).  I trust that you can address the activation issue as you see fit, so no patches are provided--just the 4 ISO files (burn them with your favorite DVD burner).




